speech: As a beginner, start with bodyweight exercises and focus on form.
Intermediate level workouts should include progressive resistance training and cardio.
Beginner routines can include brisk walking, light jogging, or yoga to build stamina and flexibility.
Focus on compound exercises like deadlifts, pull-ups, and bench presses. Include cardio for endurance
Experts can explore advanced routines like Olympic lifting, CrossFit, or triathlon training.
Consider periodized training plans to target strength, endurance, and recovery systematically.
